On the Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. National Day of Service, President Obama, Cabinet Secretaries, and other senior administration officials participated in community service projects and events throughout the country. The day is an opportunity for all Americans to come together to help meet the needs of their communities and make an ongoing commitment to service throughout the year. The First Family participated in a community service project at the Browne Education Campus in Washington, DC, while the Vice President and Dr. Jill Biden traveled to Philadelphia to participate in the 17th annual Greater Philadelphia Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Day of Service. Cabinet Secretaries and Senior Administration Officials also participated in various service events across the country.